eded to explain the size distribution of shells in the SMC. Further comparison with largely incomplete H I data for M31, M33 and Holmberg II also shows agreement in the slopes, but perhaps hinting at systematic differences between spiral and Im galaxies. We estimate porosities that are substantially {\textless} 1 for all of the galaxies except Holmberg II, for which we obtain values ≳ 1. Most of these galaxies therefore may not be strongly dominated by a hot interstellar component. However, porosity results for the Galaxy remain inconclusive with the available data. {\textcopyright} 1997 RAS.},
